<item>
            <title>[HIVE-3230] Make logging of plan progress in HadoopJobExecHelper configurable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-3230</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, by default, every second a job is run a massive JSON string containing the query plan, the tasks, and some counters is logged to the hive_job_log.  For large, long running jobs that can easily reach gigabytes of data. This logging should be configurable as average user doesn&apos;t need this logging.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
